reductions over which they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">have had little or no influence, although across the West Mercia region recorded crime has fallen for several consecutive years, long before the election of the PCC.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Over the past 12 months recorded crime has fal</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">len approximately 7% across West Mercia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 31.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">In terms of delivering an effective police service, the Commissioner has worked closely with the Chief Constable and his senior management team and has given public support to a recent restructure of policing services across the West Mercia and Warwickshire Alliance. The new operational policing model has been only been in place since 1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> October 2013 so we only have early indications rather than meaningful data, however, the initial signs are that response times and other key performance indicators have not been negatively affected. Further reports and detailed performance information will be provided to the Panel on a regular basis over the next 12 months to ensure that any emerging issues are picked up and challenged.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 31.34pt; padding-left:4.66pt; te