span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> The Deputy Commissioner has been an integral part of this approach, with West Mercia providing a challenge in terms of the sheer size of the region, albeit with a relatively low population. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Having a Deputy working closely with the Commissioner has enabled a much greater degree of engagement with stakeholders. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The PCC has already produced a Community </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Engagement Strategy which includes the appointment of 6 Community Ambassadors to act as the PCC's "eyes and ears" and feed local information back to the Commissioner's Office. It is also worth noting that the 6 Ambassadors have been appointed at very little cost</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and all 6 have well established networks across local partnerships, which the Panel view as extremely positive.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Progress on establishing collaboration agreements with other commissioners, policing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> organisations and partners. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">There are g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ood working relationships between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">PCC and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ommunity Safety Partnerships</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size: